										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In honor of April Fools, here&#8217;s a bit of fun!  Browsing a bit too much, I came across some funny old photos that really caught my eye.  Victoriana has so many sides to it, it&#8217;s sometimes easy to forget a few.  First off, not sure if it&#8217;s really Victorian or Edwardian, but here&#8217;s a &#8220;Victorian photobomb&#8221; I found on Memebase.</p>
<p style="text-align:left;"><a href="http://cheezburger.com/7192075264" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter" alt="" src="https://i.chzbgr.com/maxW500/7192075264/h22AE1164/" width="500" height="402" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align:left;">This girl has her own brand of swag.  I bet she could tell you some stories.  And I think the pearls set off the jungle scene fantastically, don&#8217;t you?</p>
<p style="text-align:center;"><a href="http://tatestreethighsociety.com/2013/01/29/chicagos-poetry-whores/" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter" alt="" src="http://tatestreethighsociety.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/tattoo-victorian.jpg" width="360" height="453" /></a></p>
<p>Last but surely not least, Victorian Surrealism!!  Oh boy, oh boy!  The internet loves me.  It gives me all the nicest thing!  All I can say is that I want more.  Click the image to see other wonderful bits of bizarre by the fantastic artist,  Jeffrey Michael Harp.</p>
<p><a href="http://pulpfactor.com/photography/6617/victorian-surrealism-by-jeffrey-michael-harp/"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter" alt="" src="http://pulpfactor.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/Surrealistic-art-by-Jeffrey-Michael-Harp.jpg" width="600" height="442" /></a></p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
